During the course basic grammar knowledge is given through a range of activities and exercises e.g. reading texts on a variety of topics listed below and listening to dialogues. Communicative approach is used in teaching speaking and listening skills. 
The topics covered during the course: 
- Languages, countries, nationalities
- Town, address, occupation
- Family, relatives
- Numbers, colours
- Food and beverages, in a shop, in a cafe
- Time
- Transport, bus station, taxi
- Location
Students are also given a brief overview of the main aspects of Lithuanian culture and everyday life.Objectives/eesmärkid:  A course in Lithuanian for Beginners is  for those students who do not speak Lithuanian or have only minimal knowledge. The aim of the course is to give basic knowledge of Lithuanian and to develop all four language skills (reading, writing, listening, speaking) through a variety of tasks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student is able to understand simple written and oral texts in Lithuanian and to use the vocabulary and grammar covered during the course in simple everyday communication situations.
